<h2>Issues</h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<h3>zurb-foundation gem does not require <code>jquery.foundation.topbar.js</code></h3>
		<p>A patch is to require it manually in <code>application.js</code> manifest file.</p>
		<p><code>//= require foundation/jquery.foundation.topbar</code></p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h3>When in responsive mobile view, the expand arrow in top bar does not show</h3>
		<p>In the docs under <%= link_to 'navigation', 'http://foundation.zurb.com/docs/navigation.php' %>, navigate to "top bar" and then "basic needs". It states <q>the <code>li.toggle-topbar</code> element that will expand the menu in the repsonsive layout.</q> However, in the templates, the arrow has a class of <code>toggle-nav</code>.</p>
		<p>To remedy this, change the class of the arrow to <code>toggle-topbar</code>, as stated in the docs.</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h3>When in responsive mobile view, top bar does not expand when clicking on the arrow</h3>
		<p>Top bar is not initiated automatically. You must add the following code to be executed after requiring foundation. Thanks to @mhayes.</p>
		<p>
			<pre><code>
$(document).ready(function() {
	$(document).foundationTopBar()
});
			</pre></code>
		</p>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h3>Applying the <code>top-bar contain-to-grid</code> classes to the top bar nav results in the viewport being expanded to the right</h3>
		<p>Issue does not occur when <code>top-bar contain-to-grid fixed</code> classes is applied to the top bar nav. @zurbchris is looking to add a fix for the issue this week. I'll update if a fix for the issue is found.</p>
	</li>
</ul>

